This paper is primarily focused on the formal study of SPARQL, which is a query language for RDF (Resource Description Framework) data. This makes it relevant to the database (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses complexity bounds and optimization procedures, which are topics that fall under the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper provides a compositional semantics for SPARQL, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO).
